HEADWORD: Catawba
<hw>Ca*taw"ba</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A well
known light red variety of American grape.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A light-colored, sprightly American wine from the
